ble plainrowheaders\" style=\"width:100%;\"\n|- style=\"color:#FFFFFF;\"\n! style=\"background:#FF5795;\"| Episode\n! style=\"background:#FF5795;\"| Title\n! style=\"background:#FF5795;\"| Written by\n! style=\"background:#FF5795;\"| Directed by\n! style=\"background:#FF5795;\"| Original airdate\n{{Episode list\n | EpisodeNumber= 1\n | Title= The Wheeler Dealers\n | Aux1= Murray Smith\n | Aux2= Sally Taylor\n | OriginalAirDate= {{Start date|1979|1|9|df=y}}\n | ShortSummary= With Rainbow growing increasingly frustrated at their unorthodox methods, Bulman, Willis and Doran are on a case involving illegally imported goods. Bulman's head is turned by a lady doctor who is involved in the case. \n | LineColor=FF5795\n}}\n{{Episode list\n | EpisodeNumber= 2\n | Title= Call of the Wild\n | Aux1= Leslie Duxbury\n | Aux2= Baz Taylor\n | OriginalAirDate= {{Start date|1979|1|16|df=y}}\n | ShortSummary= Bulman goes undercover with a gang to gather evidence for a number of robberies, and finds himself involved in the perpetration of one of them - which unbeknownst to him, Singer is pursuing.\n | LineColor=FF5795\n}}\n{{Episode list\n | EpisodeNumber= 3\n | Title= Clever Dick\n | Aux1= Brian Finch\n | Aux2= Quentin Lawrence\n | OriginalAirDate= {{Start date|1979|1|23|df=y}}\n | ShortSummary= When a hotshot former colleague of Bulman's comes up from London to take the lead in a counterfeit case, Bulman's annoyance is matched by his curiosity as to why.\n | LineColor=FF5795\n}}\n{{Episode list\n | EpisodeNumber= 4\n | Title= Friends in High Places\n | Aux1= Murray Smith\n | Aux2= Bill Gilmour\n | OriginalAirDate= {{Start date|1979|1|30|df=y}}\n | ShortSummary= Bulman and Willis are on the trail of the attacker of a youth in a hotel public toilet, unaware that there are other interested parties, for other reasons.\n | LineColor=FF5795\n}}\n{{Episode list\n | EpisodeNumber= 5\n | Title= Marriages, Deaths and Births\n | Aux1= Murray Smith\n | Aux2= [[Charles Sturridge]]\n | OriginalAir