et the candidates for the Kids' Choice Awards Argentina |url=http://www.infobae.com/2012/08/11/664179-se-conocieron-los-candidatos-los-kids-choice-awards-argentina |website=[[Infobae]] |date=August 11, 2012 |language=spanish |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160309063604/http://www.infobae.com/2012/08/11/664179-se-conocieron-los-candidatos-los-kids-choice-awards-argentina |archivedate=March 9, 2016 |url-status=live  }}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"13\"|2013\n| rowspan=\"4\"|[[40th Annie Awards|Annie Award]]\n| Best Animated Television Production for Children\n| For \"[[Princess Cookie]]\"\n| {{nom}}\n| <ref>{{cite web|last=Busis|first=Hillary|title=Annie Award Nominees Announced {{en dash}} Wreck-It Ralph, Brave, & More|url=http://ew.com/article/2012/12/03/annie-awards-nominees/|work=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|date=December 3, 2012|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170329083532/http://ew.com/article/2012/12/03/annie-awards-nominees/|archivedate=March 29, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n| Design in an Animated Television/Broadcast Production\n| For \"[[The Hard Easy (Adventure Time)|The Hard Easy]]\"\n| {{nom}}\n| <ref>{{cite web|title=Annie Award Nominations Unveiled |url=http://deadline.com/2012/12/2012-annie-award-nominations-381176/ |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]  |date=December 3, 2012 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160203024642/http://deadline.com/2012/12/2012-annie-award-nominations-381176/ |archivedate=February 3, 2016 |url-status=live  }}</ref>\n|-\n| Storyboarding in an Animated Television/Broadcast Production\n| For \"[[Goliad (Adventure Time)|Goliad]]\"\n| {{nom}}\n| <ref name=\"latimes1\">{{cite news|last=King |first=Susan |title='Brave,' 'Wreck-It Ralph' Among Nominees for the Annie Awards |url=http://articles.latimes.com/2012/dec/03/entertainment/la-et-mn-brave-wreck-it-ralph-nominees-annie-awards-20121202/4  |newspaper=[[Los Angeles Times]] |date=December 3, 2012 |archivedate=March 5, 2016 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/2