"\n|-\n!  style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"|Year\n!  style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"|Chart\n!  style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"|Position\n|-  style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"\n||2006\n||Top Independent Albums\n||45\n|}\n\n'''Album''' - [[Music recording sales certification]]s\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:350px;\"\n|-\n!  style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"|Year\n!  style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"|Country\n!  style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"|Award\n!  style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"|Number sold\n|-\n|  style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"|2006\n|  style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"|Cyprus\n|  style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"|Gold\n|  style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"|5,000 copies<ref name=BW&BK/>\n|-  style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top;\"\n||2007\n||Brazil\n||Gold\n||50,000 copies\n|}\n\n== Credits ==\n===Sepultura===\n* [[Derrick Green]] - [[Singing|vocals]]\n* [[Andreas Kisser]] - [[Electric guitar|guitar]]s, horns arrangements, strings arrangements\n* [[Paulo Jr.]] - [[Bass guitar|bass]]\n* [[Igor Cavalera]] - [[Drum kit|drums]]\n\n===Additional personnel===\n{{Div col|colwidth=35em}}\n====[[Horn (instrument)|Horn]]s====\n* Luiz Garcia \n* Samuel Hamzem\n\n====[[Cellists]]====\n* Fabio Presgrave \n* Bia Rebello \n\n====[[Crew]]====\n* Guilherme Cersosimo \n* Estevam Romera \n* Rogerinho Motorhead \n* Pedro Verdone  \n\n====Others====\n* Andr\u00e9 Moraes - percussion, piano, programming, sitar, Fender Rhodes, horns arrangements, strings arrangements, introduction, minimoog, producer\n* Stephan Doitschinoff - paintings\n* Mauricio Cersosimo - pre-production\n* Susanne Kammer - design\n* Stanley Soares - producer, engineer, mixing\n\n====Assistants====\n* Fragata\n* Helio Leite\n\n{{div col end}}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20061011181407/http://www.spv.de/eng/sepultura/default.html Official SPV Dante XXI Site]\n\n{{Sepultura}}\n{{Divine Comedy navbox}}\n\n[[Category:Sepultura albums]]\n[[Category:2006 albums]]\n[[Category:Concept albums]]\n[[Category:SPV/Steamhammer albums]]\n[[Category:Musical settings of poems by Dante Alighieri]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox album\n| name       = Dante XXI\n| type       = studio\n| artist     = [[Sepultura]]\n| cover      = Sepultura - Dante XXI.jpg\n| alt        =\n| released   = March 14, 2006\n| recorded   = 2005\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = {{flatlist|\n*[[Groove metal]]\n*[[thrash metal]]<ref name=about />\n}}\n| length     = 39:06\n| label      = [[SPV GmbH|SPV]]\n| producer   = Andr\u00e9 Moraes, Sepultura, Stanley Soares\n| prev_title = [[Live in S\u00e3o Paulo (Sepultura album)|Live in S\u00e3o Paulo]]\n| prev_year  = 2005\n| next_title = [[The Best of Sepultura]]\n| next_year  = 2006\n}}\n'''''Dante XXI''''' is the tenth studio album by the Brazilian [[Heavy metal music|metal]] band [[Sepultura]], released in 2006 through [[SPV GmbH|SPV Records]]. It is a [[concept album]] based on the three sections of [[Dante Alighieri]]'s ''[[The Divine Comedy]]''; ''[[The Divine Comedy#Inferno|Inferno]]'' (hell), ''[[Purgatorio]]'' (purgatory) and ''[[Paradiso (Dante)|Paradiso]]'' (paradise). This is the last album to feature [[Igor Cavalera]] on drums.\n\n==Album information==\n''Dante XXI'' was originally titled \"Dante 05\", but was changed when it became clear that the album would not be released by the end of 2005. The first single from the album was \"Convicted in Life\". A video for the song was released in 2006, and it won the [[MTV]] ''VMB'' Best Editing in a Video Award that year.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bonde.com.br/bonde.php?id_bonde=1-2--302-20060929 |title=Pitty faz a festa no VMB 2006 - Divers\u00e3o e Cultura |publisher=Bonde.com.br |date=29 September 2006 |accessdate=13 December 2011}}</ref> In January 2008 the band released a music video for the song \"Ostia\". The album artwork was done by Stephan Doitschinoff, whom the band commissioned to do 10 paintings based on the ''[[Divine Comedy]]''.\n\nCovers of [[Judas Priest]]'s \"[[Screaming for Vengeance]]\" and [[Sick of It All]]'s \"Scratch the Surface\" have been recorded as B-sides. \"Screaming for Vengeance\" was added as a Japanese bonus track, while \"Scratch the Surface\" is included on the SOIA tribute album ''[[Our Impact Will Be Felt]]''.\nThe Brazilian edition (Krako records), contains two bonus tracks: \"Mindwar\" (recorded live from Stanley Soares's mixing desk in Ehfurt/Germany, December 3, 2004 on tour with Motorhead) and \"False\" (demo recorded at High Five Studio S\u00e3o Paulo, during pre production for Dante XXI July 2005).\n\nInitial ideas for the album included a [[symphonic metal]] album (like [[Metallica]]'s [[S&M (Metallica album)|S&M album]]), and a concept album based on the novel ''[[A Clockwork Orange (novel)|A Clockwork Orange]]'', which was applied to their next studio album ''[[A-Lex]]''.{{cn|date=November 2015}}\n\n== Reception ==\n{{Album ratings\n|rev1 = [[About.com]]\n|rev1score = {{Rating|4.5|5}}<ref name=about>{{cite web|last=Bowar|first=Chad|title=Sepultura - Dante XXI|url=http://heavymetal.about.com/od/cdreviews/gr/sepultura.htm|work=About.com|accessdate=August 9, 2013}}</ref>\n|rev2 = [[AllMusic]]\n|rev2score = {{Rating|3.5|5}}<ref name=AllMusic>{{cite web|last=Huey|first=Steve|title=Sepultura: Dante XXI|url=http://www.allmusic.com/album/dante-xxi-mw0000756595|work=AllMusic|accessdate=August 9, 2013}}</ref>\n|rev3 = ''[[Alternative Press (music magazine)|Alternative Press]]''\n|rev3score = {{Rating|4|5}}<ref name=Press>{{cite web|last=Freeman |first=Phil |title=Sepultura - Dante XXI |url=http://altpress.com/reviews/197.htm |work=Alternative Press |accessdate=August 9, 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20060621051741/http://altpress.com/reviews/197.htm |archivedate=June 21, 2006 }}</ref>\n|rev4 = [[Blabbermouth.net]]\n|rev4score = (7/10)<ref name=Blabbermouth>{{cite web|last=Kaye|first=Don|title=Sepultura: Dante XXI|url=http://www.blabbermouth.net/showreview.aspx?reviewID=618|work=Blabbermouth.net|accessdate=August 9, 2013}}</ref>\n|rev5 = ''[[Brave Words & Bloody Knuckles]]''\n|rev5score = (8.5/10)<ref>{{cite web|last=Popoff|first=Martin|title=Sepultura: Dante XXI|url=http://www.bravewords.com/hardwares/1000969|work=Brave Words & Bloody Knuckles|accessdate=August 9, 2013}}</ref>\n|rev6 = [[Metal Storm (webzine)|Metal Storm]]\n|rev6score = (8.5/10)<ref name=\"Metal Storm\">{{cite web|last=Collin|title=Sepultura - Dante XXI|url=http://www.metalstorm.net/pub/review.php?review_id=625&page=&message_id=|work=Metal Storm|accessdate=August 9, 2013}}</ref>\n|rev7 = [[Stylus Magazine]]\n|rev7score = C\u2212<ref name=Stylus>{{cite web|last=Lee |first=Cosmo |title=Sepultura: Dante XXI |url=http://www.stylusmagazine.com/reviews/sepultura/dante-xxi.htm |work=Stylus Magazine |accessdate=August 9, 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130629062342/http://www.stylusmagazine.com/reviews/sepultura/dante-xxi.htm |archivedate=June 29, 2013 }}</ref>\n}}\n\nMany critics stated that it was the best [[Derrick Green]]-era Sepultura album thus far. Chad Bowar from [[About.com]] praised the album for its intensity and commented that it \"brings the thrash at full blast\". He also highlighted Green's vocal performance, as well as the album's overall concept.<ref name=about/> [[AllMusic]]'s Steve Huey noted that much of the elements that made Sepultura \"stand out from the metal pack\" are still present on this record, and that this was one of Sepultura's strongest releases with Green on vocals.<ref name=AllMusic/>\n\n''[[Alternative Press (music magazine)|Alternative Press]]'' reviewer Phil Freeman stated that with this album, Sepultura are \"finally back at full strength\", giving the listener \"exactly what he hopes to get from pioneers in the art of skull-crushing\".<ref name=Press/> In a mixed review for [[Stylus Magazine]], Cosmo Lee said that the riffs were \"unmemorable\" and the songs lacked \"tension and release\". He also criticized the album's artwork, describing it as a \"weak, mild-mannered font worthy of indie rock\".<ref name=Stylus/>\n\nDespite mostly positive reviews, sales of the album were disappointing and continued the decrease in sales of Sepultura's albums since ''[[Against (album)|Against]]'', selling only 2,300 copies its first week of release in the US.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.roadrunnerrecords.com/Blabbermouth.net/news.aspx?mode=Article&newsitemID=113708|title=SEPULTURA: 'A-Lex' First-Week Sales Revealed|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090211122031/http://www.roadrunnerrecords.com/BlabberMouth.Net/news.aspx?mode=Article&newsitemID=113708|archivedate=2009-02-11}}</ref> Dante XXI has sold 120,000+ copies worldwide as of January 2, 2008 and went ''Gold'' in [[Brazil]] and [[Cyprus]] (their first music industry certification outside of Brazil since ''Roots'').<ref name=BW&BK>{{cite news|url=http://www.bravewords.com/news/62604 |title=Sepultura - Dante XXI Certified Gold in Cyprus |date=21 March 2007 |publisher=[[Brave Words & Bloody Knuckles]] |accessdate=23 January 2009}}</ref>\n\nAccording to Matthew Teutsch, a scholar of literature and popular culture, the album is \"a modern-day soundtrack for Dante\u2019s Divine Comedy\" and allows an exploration of the poem \"through an aesthetic rendering of twenty-first-century national (and international) issues\".<ref name=\"teutsch2\">{{cite journal|first=Matthew|last=Teutsch|url=https://latchjournal.files.wordpress.com/2015/07/matthew-teutsch-dante-in-a-modern-context.pdf|title=Dante in a Modern Context: A Review of Sepultura's Album Dante XXI|journal=LATCH: A Journal for the Study of the Literary, Artifact in Theory, Culture, or History|volume=8|year=2008|pages=159-80|accessdate=March 29, 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Track listing ==\n{{tracklist\n| all_music = [[Andreas Kisser]], [[Derrick Green]], [[Igor Cavalera]], except where noted\n| title1 = Lost (Intro)\n| lyrics1 = (instrumental)\n| length1 = 0:59\n| title2 = Dark Wood of Error\n| lyrics2 = Kisser\n| length2 = 2:18\n| title3 = [[Convicted in Life]]\n| lyrics3 = Kisser, Green\n| length3 =  3:09\n| title4 = City of Dis\n| lyrics4 = Green\n| length4 = 3:27\n| title5 = False\n| lyrics5 = Kisser\n| length5 = 3:34\n| title6 = Fighting On\n| lyrics6 = Green\n| length6 = 4:29\n| title7 = [[Limbo]] (Intro)\n| lyrics7 = (instrumental)\n| length7 = 0:44\n| title8 = Ostia\n| lyrics8 = Kisser\n| length8 = 3:07\n| title9 = Buried Words\n| lyrics9 = Green\n| length9 = 2:35\n| title10 = Nuclear Seven\n| lyrics10 = Kisser\n| length10 = 3:44\n| title11 = Repeating the Horror\n| lyrics11 = Green\n| length11 = 3:11\n| title12 = Euno\u00e9 (Intro)\n| lyrics12 = (instrumental)\n| length12 = 0:13\n| title13 = Crown and Miter\n| lyrics13 = Green\n| note13 = Kisser, Green, Cavalera, [[Paulo Jr.]]\n| length13 = 2:12\n| title14 = Primium Mobile (Intro)\n| lyrics14 = (instrumental)\n| length14 = 0:29\n| title15 = Still Flame\n| lyrics15 = Kisser\n| note15 = Kisser, Andr\u00e9 Moraes\n| length15 = 4:51\n}}\n\n{{tracklist\n| headline = Japanese/Korean bonus track\n| title16 = [[Screaming for Vengeance]]\n| length16 = 3:31 \n| note16 = [[Judas Priest]] cover \n| lyrics16 = Halford\n| music16 = Downing, Tipton <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cdjapan.co.jp/detailview.html?KEY=VICP-63397 |title=Dante XXI Sepultura [CD&#93; |publisher=Cdjapan.co.jp |accessdate=13 December 2011}}</ref>\n}}\n\n{{tracklist\n| headline = Brazilian bonus tracks\n| title16 = Mind War (Live)\n| length16 = 3:01\n| lyrics16 = Kisser, Green\n| music16 = Kisser, Green, Cavalera, Paulo Jr. \n| title17 = False (Demo)\n| length17 = 3:15 \n| lyrics17 = Kisser\n| music17 = Kisser, Green, Cavalera \n}}\n\n{{tracklist\n| headline = Our Impact Will Be Felt track\n| title